
sitemesh-theme
------------------------------------------------------

This project extends sitemesh (http://www.opensymphony.com/sitemesh/) 
to enable code reuse via website themes... aka "private labels".

It allows you to host multiple domains with distinct designs
from a single web application.

This enables:
1) reusing front-end code and resources (HTML, CSS, images, etc)
2) reduced deployment time
3) scale (run multiple websites in one JVM without the overhead of multiple webapps)

Building
-----------------------------------------------------
sitemesh-theme uses a Gradle build:  http://www.gradle.org/

Once Gradle is Installed use the command:

gradle build


The sitemesh-theme.jar will be in the build/lib directory

Dependencies
-----------------------------------------------------
sitemesh-2.4.2
commons-collections-3.2
commons-logging-1.1



